The recurring word I see in these repeated phrases is judges.
```
Count  Phrase
45     year of the reign of the judges over the people of Nephi
100    the reign of the judges
141    judges
```


Here is the first and last paragraphs that mention the word judges.

First paragraph:
```
29:11 Therefore I will be your king the remainder of my days;
nevertheless, let us appoint judges, to judge this people according to
our law; and we will newly arrange the affairs of this people, for we
will appoint wise men to be judges, that will judge this people
according to the commandments of God.
```

Last paragraph:
```
27:27 And know ye that ye shall be judges of this people, according to
the judgment which I shall give unto you, which shall be just.
Therefore, what manner of men ought ye to be? Verily I say unto you,
even as I am.
```

Imagine the young Mormon people establishing a successful community in 1823. A 17-year old
Joseph Smith was focused on creating laws that support the community. This reminds
me of a quote from Socrates:
```
Those who are too smart to engage in politics are punished by being governed by those who are dumber
```
I believe that BoM spirit would approve of that message as well.

The BoM is about setting up a community (nation?) of people with a shared values from the people from
Israel. When I think of trouble with national politics, a constitution that is not resolving problems quickly, and a border that is out of control, I see politics as an essential topic for all citizen, young and old, powerful and meek, everyone.

